The course presents an overview of various types of texts, their teaching methods and possibilities of using them in the frames of the Estonian course curriculum of the general education schools.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide an overview of text types represented in the school curriculum and an ability to analyze and teach different texts. The course gives an overview of different methods of text instruction and their applications.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course student - knows the current Estonian language and literature curriculum and its text instruction component; - knows methods of text instruction; - knows how to apply contemporary methods in text analysis and instruction; - knows the instructor's role in teaching texts and is competent in one's role as an instructor.
